race.comment: BELVEDERE ROCK (2) had a bit on his rivals last time with an impressive 4 lengths win over 1614m at this track. Has been in super form this campaign and he still has plenty of scope for improvement being a lightly raced commodity. Can continue to raise the bar and bring up a hat-trick of wins. MORE LIKELY (3) finished 3 lengths away in fourth last time out over 1400m at Kalgoorlie after being prominent at the bend a month ago. Steps up in journey today but should appreciate the easier company he's facing. Can put his best foot forward form an inside draw. NEVER SOBER (6) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a head from the winner in third over 1410m at this track. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. TIGER LINE (4) has not won for a long while. Last raced on October 23 when fourth  at this track over 1614m. Best figures measure up nicely. In the mix. BENTLEY BEAU (5) was good late last start and is not to be discounted.
